👏🏀 Give a round of applause to our Athlyt of the week, professional international basketball player, @i_am_gene_campbell 🌟 Hailing from Jersey City, NJ Eugene played his college ball for New Jersey City University and is now playing for Club Basket Albufeira in Portugal! A man of many talents and passions, Eugene is also the CEO and Founder of Walkamilenourshoes Inc., a non-profit organization that delivers sneakers, clothes, and essentials to those in need across the world. 🌎 Eugene is proving that athletes can impact others in deep and profound ways, and we couldn't  be more proud of him for doing that! ❗️Attention to Details❗️

@jasonmkoval asked what the biggest differences were at each level of basketball, and this is Eugene Campbell III’s response to that question!! 

Just a reminder that you’ll be able to catch the full interview tomorrow when it drops at 6:00 AM (MST). It’s an awesome opportunity to hear from @i_am_gene_campbell and learn about his journey, as it may be a similar one that many other athletes have to take! But the amazing thing is, he shows us all, that it IS POSSIBLE!! 

Also want to give a shoutout to @athlyt.co which is where I first saw and heard of Eugene’s story. Give them a follow as well, especially if you are interested in learning more about what they can bring to the table for you in regards to NIL 

#GTG #Basketball

🚨 Eugene Campbell III 🚨

Professional basketball player, Eugene Campbell III is on the podcast this week and this question was brought to you by my dude @griffin.deere (who is a multi sport athlete at Meridian HS in Meridian, ID) 

If you want to play in the pros, you need to tap in and hear what it’s like to train like a pro because Eugene will share his story with you which includes information on what the transition was like to the professional level, and how he’s dealt with that. 

He also gives a lot of insight as to what to do when you’re looking for an agent, and how to find one that’s trustworthy (which is an EXTREMELY important piece to this thing, and often overlooked) 

You can find the show on your favorite podcast platform!! 

Make sure to give a follow to @athlyt.co as well, which is where I found out about Eugene and many other amazing athletes!!

Follow: @walkamilenourshoes
